title: Art Institute of Chicago Collection Coaster Set
description:
Our 6 piece coaster set is developed from:  Vincent van Gogh’s The Bedroom, 1899; Pierre-Auguste Renoir’s Two Sisters (On the Terrace), 1881; Georges Seurat’s A Sunday on La Grande Jatte—1884, 1884-86; Paul Cezanne’s The Basket of Apples, 1893; Claude Monet’s Water Lilies, 1906 and The Artist’s House at Argenteuil, 1873, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Locate your glass with a unique piece of artwork.  A winning combination: durable, practical and beautiful.

  • 6 coasters and images.
  • Dimensions: 3.75 x 3.75 in.
  • Materials: High density fiber board, non-slip cork backing.
